# amtm and its modules are POSIX shell scripts for Asuswrt-Merlin routers.
# They MUST be served with LF line endings: the router keeps an LF copy
# (amtm runs dos2unix on its own files) and compares its MD5 against the raw
# file fetched from x-crm.in. CRLF here would make the hashes never match,
# producing a permanent phantom "MD5 upd" on every run and risking a broken
# shebang during bootstrap. Force LF regardless of the committer's platform.
amtm    text eol=lf
*.mod   text eol=lf
